  <abstract>Gibson served in HQ Detachment, 6th Div., Regular Army. He was born in Campbell County, Tennessee but his draft card lists a Cleveland, Ohio address and place of business. He received an honorable discharge December 2, 1918. He was raised in Knox County, Tennessee. Gibson describes daily activities in France. He mentions visiting the Eiffel Tower, joining a YMCA party, and seeing picture shows. He also makes daily notations about the weather. He is buried at Mount Olive Cemetery in South Knoxville, Tenn.</abstract>
